
This package/port comes all working out of the box. By default it 
is using a free, non-logged, uncensored resolver over IPv4 only.

Other resolvers are also available. Please check the CSV list at 
%%PREFIX%%/share/dnscrypt-proxy/dnscrypt-resolvers.csv if you want to 
customize the resolver to be used.

To redirect a local resolver through dnscrypt-proxy:
	# ifconfig lo0 127.0.53.1/32 alias
	# sysrc dnscrypt_proxy_flags="-a 127.0.53.1"
	# service dnscrypt-proxy onestart

To enable dnscrypt-proxy (redirecting local resolver) at boot:
	# sysrc dnscrypt_proxy_enable="YES"
	# sysrc dnscrypt_proxy_flags="-a 127.0.53.1"
	# sysrc ifconfig_lo0_alias0="inet 127.0.53.1/32"

To view available options:
	# %%PREFIX%%/sbin/dnscrypt-proxy --help
	  or
	# man dnscrypt-proxy

